CLI & GIT

* make a new directory
  - mkdir <directory name>

* open a directory
  - cd <directory name>
  - cd .. // go back one directory
  - cd ../../.. // go back three directories

* open the directory in IDE
  - code .

* list of all contents in the directory
  - ls

* add git branch
  - git branch <branch name>
  - git branch -a // all branches

* git status of branches and changes needed
  - git status

* log of all commits
  - git log

* commit
  - git commit -m "text"
  - git commit . // commit all

* add changes
  - git add <file name>
  - git add . // add all

* switch branches
  - git checkout <branch name>

* delete branch unmerged
  - git branch -D <branch name>
  - git branch -d <branch name> // merged commits

* create new branch and switch to it
   git checkout -b <branch name>
